Repos 
|                                        |
Software collections (scl utils)         yum
package/v1
package/v2 <- enabled

Enable a repo which has the yum packages 
subscription-manager repos --enable rhel-server-rhscl-7-rpms 

Install python 
yum install rh-python35-python-pip 
yum install software_collection_1\* 

Remove
yum remove software_collection_1\* 

Enable scl utils 
yum install scl-utils

Syntax for scl
scl action software_collection_1 software_collection_2 command 
scl action software_collection_1 software_collection_2 'command --args' 
scl action software_collection_1 software_collection_2 -- command --args

List all software collections
scl -l 
List all enabled in current sessions 
echo $X_SCLS 

Enable a package for running command/ starting bash
scl enable rh-python36 bash
scl enable software_collection_1 'perl --version' 
scl enable software_collection_1 software_collection_2 bash 
cat cmd | scl enable software_collection_1 - 

Enable a package forrunning command from shell with persisted source
$ cat /etc/profile.d/enablepython33.sh
#!/bin/bash
source scl_source enable python33

Install pip
pip install package

Update
pip install package-name -U
pip install package-name -upgrade

https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_software_collections/3/html/packaging_guide/sect-enabling_support_for_software_collections
https://access.redhat.com/solutions/1519803
